The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Calcutta crash
                                                                                                               Calcutta crash
                            
	Calcutta, Aug. 21: A pedestrian was killed tonight when a bus hit from behind by a gas tanker rammed into him.        
	Tapan Sarkar, 40, a resident of Kidderpore, was declared dead in hospital. The mishap, at the Kidderpore crossing, occurred around 8.30pm.        
	Near National Medical College in Park Circus, Basanta Sinha, 35, was mowed down by a bus while crossing the road.         
	Hospital hot chase        
	Twenty Trinamul activists today chased three CPM cadres through an emergency ward packed with patients, forcing the trio to take shelter in the Hooghly hospitals kitchen.        
	The three  two cadres and the third who wanted to see a doctor at the block hos-pital in Jangipara for bruises suffered in a clash last nighthad to be rescued by police. The five patients looked on stunned as they ran, said Sheikh Amir, a patients relative.                                                                                                                                                                             
